title: For Sale:  Dillon Rapid Trim 1200
postcontent:
Makes short work out of trimming large quantities of rifle brass. 
The RT 1200 is used just like a standard size die. The big difference is that while you are pushing the case into the die to size it, a 1/4 horsepower electric motor driving a carbide cutter is trimming the case to length. Chips are drawn off through a vacuum manifold that clamps to the outside of the special size/trim die. Outside diameter of manifold as 1.250" 
The RT1200 is equipped with a quick-disconnect power cord; and it can be used on any standard reloader, single stage or progressive.

Trim Dies:
30-30, .308, 30-06

title: For Sale/Trade:  Your overpriced gun for my amusement
postcontent:
You: opportunistic dumbass who racked up several thousand dollars in debt trying to cash in on a tragedy that sparked a flood of panic buying.

Me: A guy who knows the real value of the NIB gear I'm seeing start to spring up here.  Using round figures, most of what I see is at least twice the retail value.  Any "carbon" or "plastic" AR-15 would retail for around $700.  Those were the CHEAP guns.

I'm going to guess that a lot of these guns need to be sold long before any interested party really needs to buy them.  Credit card bills, mortgages and property taxes are coming due.  I hope those guns are warm and tasty, because you may wind up eating them or living in them.

And trying to drive up your price with "make an offer," that's what gunbroker is for.  But you're too scared to face the fact that you're on the downside of this panic, and your investments are depreciating quickly.  You don't want to risk an auction because you know it's possible you won't break even.  If you manage to recover your principle you should consider yourself fortunate.

title: For Sale:  Black Talon .45 - the original collectible version not the later SXT
postcontent: I have 6 boxes of the Original Black Talon ammo in .45 ACP. Winchester discontinued production of this ammo years ago because it was deemed as too destructive for civilian use. If memory serves me this ammo was used in a few very unfortunate mass shootings in the 90's to devastating effect.
